data.text:
As a senior in 2018-19: Competed in 11 of the Red Storm’s tournaments … Finished the season with a 75.96 stroke-average across 27 rounds … Recorded the fourth-best stroke-average on the team and 37th in the BIG EAST … Shot a season-best 70 at the Wildcat Fall Invitational (Sept. 30) … Recorded nine top-40 finishes and three top-30 finishes.

As a junior in 2017-18: In 10 tournament appearances, a 76.00-stroke average was fourth best on the team… His best score came at Loyola Intercollegiate where he shot a three-round 212, with his lowest round totals of the season at 71, 71, and 70… Moore finished his junior campaign with three top-20 finishes, including a ninth place finish at the Rhode Island Invitational… At the BIG EAST Championship, he place top among his Red Storm teammates reaching as high as sixth on the overall leaderboard, but finishing tied for 12th.

Prior to St. John’s: Moore attended Nassau Community College for his first two years. While at NCC, he finished in a tie for second place at the Long Island Invitational, where he shot a two-round 151.

Personal: Full name Ross Moore…Originally from Dublin, Ireland
